Reasoning: The paper discusses a benchmark dataset for global urban analysis using machine learning techniques, specifically for the classification of local climate zones (LCZ) in remote sensing images. This involves image processing, feature extraction, and classification, which are all relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of machine learning also suggests relevance to machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques for quality assessment, indicating possible relevance to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
